reviews.comment: A must do while in NY. The building itself is absolutely perfect. Well maintained and so beautiful. The staff really nice and very professional. We loved the vue from up there and the souvenir shop is amazing. We also appreciated a lot the historic part of the visit and the entertainment one. The visit was very well conceived to be a whole experience not just a simple sightseeing which justifies the cost. Very well done.
reviews.review_reply: We appreciate this more than you could ever know! Thank you so, so much for everything you said!! We are truly honored and we are grateful that you chose to spend some time with us!! Enjoy the rest of your NYC experience!!

reviews.comment:
The Empire State Building offers one of the most stunning views in New York City! I visited with a friend, and the 360-degree panorama from the observation deck was absolutely breathtaking. From the sparkling skyline to iconic landmarks like Central Park and the Statue of Liberty, every angle was picture-perfect.

The experience was well-organized, and the staff made the process smooth despite the crowd. Visiting at sunset is a must—it’s magical watching the city lights come to life as the sun sets. The view at night is equally stunning, with the city glowing beneath you.

A true NYC icon and an unforgettable experience! Whether it’s your first time or a return visit, the Empire State Building never fails to impress.
reviews.review_reply: We are so happy that you enjoyed your visit! Thank you for sharing your experience.

reviews.comment: It was an amazing view from the Empire State Building. From the entry to the elevators they had some good history on how the Empire State Building was built. The elevator experience was also stunning. The view was awesome and they had heaters on the deck for the cold weather. They had several thrilling experiences on the top for which we need separate tickets. They have a cafe on the roof and a seating area to chill and relax. I had a great experience overall and will definitely go back.

Our visit to the Empire State Building Observatory was absolutely magical! We went after sunset, and the view of the sparkling city lights was unforgettable. The ambiance was electrifying, with an air of excitement and wonder that gave us butterflies.

The observatory itself is well-organized, and the staff made the entire experience seamless. Whether you’re a first-time visitor or a returning guest, this iconic landmark is truly a must-see. The combination of history, architecture, and those unbeatable panoramic views makes it a bucket-list destination.

Highly recommend!
reviews.review_reply: Thank you so much, Jerry!! We so appreciate all of your kind words!! They truly mean the world to us! We hope you come back to see us! Happy Holidays!

reviews.comment: This is a beautiful building. We went in February, and there was no queue. We were so lucky. The views were amazing. The staff were very nice too. There was a queue for photos with King Kongs hand, but that was all. There was no pressure to buy photos at all.
Pretty impressive on the built. Must go check it out when you are visiting NY. Highly recommended to pay extra for the 102 floor view experience. Picture taking is much nicer on the 86 floors.

reviews.comment: This was my first trip to NYC, and the Empire State Building was my favorite part! You can see NYC in a breathtaking full 360° view. The place was extremely tidy, and that allowed for clear viewing on other floors with less people. The museum as you went up really makes the experience more memorable as well, learning the history of the building. I understand and appreciate how much the Empire State Building is central to the American identity.
reviews.review_reply: Thank you so much, Axel! We are so honored to be named your favorite part of your NYC trip!! It means the world to us!

reviews.comment: Good series of history about the building, through first section. Good inside views from 80th floor then up onto observatio deck for outside view's in all directions. You can pay " a lot " extra to go up higher, which I didn't, but some might want to. Went on a clear & dry day, one of those been there seen it done it places.

What an amazing experience! This is one of those moments when you visit the first time you are in awe!

Our reservation time was for Saturday 2/15 but it was raining. When we got there the employee (I forgot her name) told us we could go up but we won’t see anything. She suggested to come back Monday and man was she right!

The most beautiful view close to sunset

reviews.comment: An amazing experience! The Empire State Building is incredibly clean and well-maintained. It was relatively quiet and not too crowded, which made it easy to take our time, explore, and enjoy the sights. Everything was well-organized and interesting, with plenty of opportunities to soak in the views. Highly recommend!
reviews.review_reply: Thank you for visiting! We are so thrilled that you had a great time with us!
